  "prompt": "Is demonetization good for economy?",
  "response": "The impacts of demonetization are complex and debated by economists. Here are some potential pros and cons:\n\nPotential Positive Effects:\n1. Reduces black money and cash hoarding\n2. Increases digital transaction transparency\n3. Reduces corruption\n4. Increases tax compliance\n5. Promotes digital financial inclusion\n\nPotential Negative Effects:\n1. Short-term economic disruption\n2. Cash shortage\n3. Reduced economic activity\n4. Impact on informal/cash-based sectors\n5. High implementation costs\n6. Temporary economic slowdown\n\nThe overall impact depends on specific implementation and economic context. Different economists and experts have varying perspectives on its effectiveness.\n\nIn India's 2016 demonetization, for example, views were sharply divided, with mixed short and long-term economic consequences.\n\nThe outcome depends on:\n- Implementation strategy\n- Economic conditions\n- Supporting policy measures\n- Duration of transition\n\nNo universal answer exists; it varies by specific national context.",
